The paper deals with the problem of creating a fair ranking of candidates, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of statistical tests to ensure fairness also suggests a potential connection to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the use of a formal problem definition and algorithm suggests a potential connection to cybernetics (cs.CY).
